tions such as LD characters dropping (those LD characters that the server can detect) and 15 minute timeouts on stuck characters in the world!  But how many times have you invited a player when you were ungrouped and been told that 'only the group leader may invite players'.  Or heard other peoples group chat?  (and you weren't grouped).  Or hit Follow and nothing happens?<br><br>2) The Great Divide, Shadowhaven, Insertzonefromhell here crash bug!  <br><br>Play a character, then switch back to a different one, then port to great divide, or zone into Shadowhaven!  I'm sure there are more such demon-zones in the game.  Wow!  Why is it taking me so long to load?  Oh, my hard drives blinking.  Well... slow..ly...wait...maybe... hmm, network connection stopped.  10 minutes later: CTRL-ALT-DEL time.  I personally experience this bug roughly 3 times a day, and seeing as Shadowhaven is a central hub of Luclin, this ,,!,, is for the programmers! <br><br>3) This one isn't exactly old but I lothe it none the less.  The so-called fixed &quot;stuck in the world for 15 minutes&quot; bug.  Crash zoning or even go LD manually, and sometimes you'll find yourself stuck in limbo to the world.  This has happened after the patch which supposedly fixed the problem.  I've personally /q'd in a place with no mobs whatsoever only to find myself stuck in the world for roughly 15 minutes while people were waiting for me.  I've crashed zoning and been stuck in limbo as well, not IN any zone, but showing up on the /who server.  I've even watched myself go LD on one comp only to seem perfectly fine, not even showing an LD tag above my characters name.   This one isn't exactly old but it drives me crazy nonetheless!<br><br>Honorable Mentions:<br><br>1) The Bandage Bug<br><br>Ever tried to bandage yourself while staying completely still?  Sorry, you've moved and interrupted your bandaging!   This bug was introduced somewhere around the time that they broke mend IIRC.  I've seen it happen every single time, and I've seen it never happen.  Probably explains why it hasn't been fixed.<br><br>2) The Invis Stacking Bug<br><br>Invis wearing off breaks sneak/hide.  Thanks for hitting me with AoE invis.  What?  My hide button is down?  But I'm visible!  Ah, another body in Western Wastes! <br><br>3) The Broken Alt XP Button<br><br>New to Luclin!  The Broken Alt XP Button!  How many times have you hit your new special ability only to have it do nothing or produce a bugged message?  Manaburn not working?  Free regen saying you can't see your target (whom happens to be yourself or standing next to you?)  I've seen people die from a broken heal button, lose duels to a broken manaburn.  I know Luclin was overly ambitious but at least fix the buttons so they're not the quick hacks that all need to be redone!  <br><br>As parting words, I would like to thank the Luclin expansion for making even Rivervale lag on a system it would have done 30+fps per second on when the game was launched!  The 3d engine just gets better and better!<br><br>Feel free to add your most annoying bugs.  <p><font size=2><B><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=98264">Tarissa Doveshadow</B></a> - 60 Assassin<br>Druzzil Ro - <a href="http://www.hossguild.com/">Hoss</a><br>Author of <a href="http://www.mob.net/~lucid/parser.html">Real-Time EQ Parser</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uglipthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glip the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pantsless Asst. Administrator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 7:02:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFro